# Google API Python Examples - Configuration Template
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env
#    $ cp example.env .env
#
# 2. Get your OAuth credentials from Google Cloud Console:
#    https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#
# 3. Fill in your CLIENT_ID and CLIENT_SECRET below
#
# 4. The .env file is gitignored and won't be committed

# ============================================================================
# Google OAuth Client Credentials (REQUIRED)
# ============================================================================
CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here.apps.googleusercontent.com
CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here
CLIENT_SCOPES=https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.readonly,https://www.googleapis.com/auth/documents.readonly,https://www.googleapis.com/auth/spreadsheets.readonly,https://www.googleapis.com/auth/presentations.readonly

# ============================================================================
# Optional: Token Storage via Environment Variables
# ============================================================================
# Use these for headless systems/containers instead of keyring
# Leave blank to use system keyring (default for local development)
# See: 08_envvar_auth.py for example usage
#
# After first OAuth flow, persist tokens by adding these to your .env:
# GOOGLEAPI_ACCESS_TOKEN=ya29.a0AfB_byC...
# GOOGLEAPI_REFRESH_TOKEN=1//0gHpZ...
#
# That's it! You don't need to store CLIENT_ID, CLIENT_SECRET, or SCOPES again.
# Those are already defined above and used during OAuth setup.
